         <div type="edition"><!-- transcription goes here; DONE -->
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>Soli Invicto
                <lb n="2"/>
               <persName type="divine">
                  <name key="Mithras">Mithrae</name>
               </persName>,
                <lb n="3"/>pro salute <persName type="imperial">
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Commodus">
                     <expan><abbr>Commod</abbr><ex>i</ex></expan>
                  </name>
                  <lb n="4"/>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Antoninus">Anton<hi rend="tall">i</hi>ni</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Augustus">
                     <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usti</ex></expan>
                  </name>
               </persName> 
                domi<hi rend="ligature">ni</hi>
               <expan><abbr><hi rend="supraline">n</hi></abbr><ex>ostri</ex></expan>;
                <lb n="5"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="praenomen" key="Marcus">
                     <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arcus</ex></expan>
                  </name>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Aurelius">
                     <expan><abbr>Aur</abbr><ex>elius</ex></expan>
                  </name>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Stertinius">Stertinius</name>
                  <lb n="6"/>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Carpus">Carpus</name>
               </persName> una cum <persName>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Carpus">Carpo</name>
               </persName>
               <lb n="7"/>
               <expan><abbr>proc</abbr><ex>uratore</ex></expan>
               <expan><abbr>k</abbr><ex>astrensi</ex></expan> patre et <persName>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Hermioneus">Her
                    <lb n="8" break="no"/>mioneo</name>
               </persName> et <persName>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Balbinus">Balb<hi rend="tall">i</hi>no</name>
               </persName> fratribus
                <lb n="9"/>
               <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>otum</ex></expan>
               <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>olvit</ex></expan>
               <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>eliciter</ex></expan>.
                
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>To the Unconquered Sun, Mithras, on behalf of the health of the emperor
                    Commodus Antoninus, our lord; Marcus Aurelius Stertinius Carpus, together with
                    Carpus, procurator of the camp, (his) father, and with Hermioneus and Balbinus,
                    (his) brothers, fulfilled (his) vow gladly.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary"><!-- notes go here -->
            <p>There is a dash on either side of the last line (- V S F -). 
                The symbol commonly used for <hi rend="italic">centuria</hi> (reminiscent of a "7") is carved below the inscription, centered, and is likely being used as a form of punctuation indicating the end of the inscription.</p>
         </div>
